\begin{alertblock}{IDEA TO BE THOUGHT ABOUT}
If triggered in an efficient way, then the principle of scattering can be used to develop technologies which can detect level/extent of water pollution caused by any macro contaminant/pollutant. For example: for a certain pollutant a specific wavelength of radiation can be selected and released in the region under observation. Now the feedback radiations received can be studied and hopefully any algorithm can be searched which can tell us the percentage of contamination by that particular pollutant in that specific region. Such methods, if developed, can prove to be of great values. 
\end{alertblock}



